<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER DOLPHINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In this world of homeless and starving people, the expensive full-page ad 
headlined "Nationwide Consumer Advisory" (Dec. 4) paid for by the Earth Island 
Institute Save the Dolphins Project headed by David Phillips really irked me! 
</P>
<P>
Whatever his dispute is with the Bumble Bee canning company I don't really care 
nor would I contribute or could afford his request for donations of $15 to $500 
or more to support his cause. As a simple day-to-day grocery shopper and using 
manufacturer's food coupons, I manage to eke out a living. To Phillips I ask, 
what is next? Save the cattle, save the sheep or save the turkeys on 
Thanksgiving Day? 
</P>
<P>
ARTHUR J. BREZAE 
</P>
<P>
West Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
