<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING BRIEFING: HE'S THROWING THE BOOK AT THE SOONERS AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TED BROCK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Games Behind the Game," a book by Walter Byers, executive director of the 
NCAA from 1951 to 1987, will be published in late summer or early fall of 1991. 
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press, the book "will deal with his suggestions for 
reform in collegiate athletics as well as look at the personalities, economic 
power and politics that influence intercollegiate sports." 
</P>
<P>
Is it ironic -- or fitting -- that "The Games Behind the Game" will be 
published by the University of Oklahoma Press? 
</P>
<P>
He broke the story: There was Woodward, there was Bernstein and now there's 
Bailey. 
</P>
<P>
Arnold Bailey of the Providence Journal-Bulletin, another in the growing legion 
of collectibles columnists, wrote in his "Collector's Corner" of Dec. 8: "Way 
back on Oct. 7, we provided a peek at what Topps is planning for 1991 -- a 
special 40th anniversary production that mixes 792 new cards with bonus samples 
of every card produced during the past four decades." 
</P>
<P>
Trivia time: There have been no tie games in the NFL this season. When was the 
last time the league went a full season without a tie? 
</P>
<P>
Way back payback: After Miami's recent 23-20 overtime victory over 
Philadelphia, the Dolphins' Jim Jensen said teammate Jeff Cross told him an 
Eagle had said Coach Buddy Ryan offered $100 to the defensive player making the 
best hit on Jensen. 
</P>
<P>
Said Ron Howard, the Eagles' media relations director: "This has absolutely 
nothing to do with Buddy Ryan. Our players felt Jim was a jerk. There was no 
bounty on him, but our players thought, yeah, if we can get a good shot on him 
within the legality of the rules and in the spirit of play, they would take 
one." 
</P>
<P>
Howard said the Eagle players were angry at Jensen for playing too rough in an 
off-season "Best of the Beach" basketball game in Jamaica. 
</P>
<P>
Add "bounty": Wednesday, the Eagles wore T-shirts that read, "Buddy's Bounty 
Hunters." 
</P>
<P>
Said guard Mike Schad: "We just found them in our lockers today. Buddy said an 
anonymous guy brought them in in a box and gave them to the PR department." 
</P>
<P>
Said Ryan: "Nobody gave me one." 
</P>
<P>
Dallas Coach Jimmy Johnson, who last year accused Ryan of putting a bounty on 
Cowboy quarterback Troy Aikman and kicker Luis Zendejas, commented on the 
T-shirts: "Was that the bounty on us or was that the one on (Jensen) we heard 
about this year?" 
</P>
<P>
The Cowboys and Eagles play Sunday in Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
Trivia answer: 1985. 
</P>
<P>
Quotebook: Princeton basketball Coach Pete Carril, explaining his team's 
deliberate style: "We're not very fast. It's like Whitey Ford. The guy didn't 
have a fastball, so he's gotta throw spitballs." TED BROCK 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
