<P>
GREEN STARTS, BUT GARY WILL PLAY A LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coach John Robinson said Thursday that Gaston Green and Cleveland Gary will 
split time at tailback Sunday at Atlanta, with Green getting the starting nod. 
</P>
<P>
"It's just going to be an even thing," Robinson said, emphasizing that neither 
Green nor Gary is ahead of the other in his mind. 
</P>
<P>
Injury report: Recently signed Bruce Klostermann will replace injured Frank 
Stams at one inside linebacker spot, Robinson said, with veteran Brett 
Faryniarz going in on passing downs. The Rams will decide today whether 
starting left guard Tom Newberry, who injured an ankle last week, can play 
Sunday. Bern Brostek, this year's No. 1 pick, will play considerably at left 
guard either way. Newberry and tight end Damone Johnson (hamstring) are both 
listed as questionable. 
</P>
<P>
For the Falcons, defensive end Mike Gann (foot) is listed as doubtful. 
Quarterback Scott Campbell (shoulder), Pro Bowl receiver Andre Rison (knee) and 
running back Steve Broussard (hamstring) are all questionable. TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
