</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TIS THE SEASON TO BE TOLERANT -- ISN'T IT? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While I sympathize with the feelings of isolation felt by many Jewish parents 
and teachers at this time of the year ("Parents Wrestle with December's 
Dilemma," Dec. 17), I must remind them that one of the themes of Hanukkah and 
other Jewish holidays is tolerance of different beliefs. 
</P>
<P>
Instead of making calls of complaint to the Jewish Federation, why isn't that 
parent making latkes, playing dreidel and teaching her child's class about 
Hanukkah? 
</P>
<P>
I have never felt guilty or wanted my children to feel guilty about enjoying 
the holidays of other religions. The more we know about the beliefs of others, 
the more we understand each other. 
</P>
<P>
VENIDA KORDA 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
