<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGUITO BASKETBALL TOURNAMENT; 
</P>
<P>
DANA HILLS MISSES GAME AFTER MIX-UP, FACES COIN FLIP TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dana Hills and San Clemente high schools will have a coin flip to decide which 
team advances in the San Dieguito boys' basketball tournament after the teams 
did not play their scheduled game Thursday because of a scheduling mix-up. 
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, we are going to have a coin flip (today)," tournament director 
David LaBorde said. 
</P>
<P>
"We were going to try to play the game (today) but couldn't get the 
arrangements made." 
</P>
<P>
The Dolphins were to play San Clemente at 7:30 p.m. Thursday at Carlsbad High 
School, but tipoff time was changed to 5:30 because of construction scheduled 
for the gymnasium. San Clemente was notified, but Dana Hills Coach Rich Skelton 
said he was not, and the Dana Hills team arrived at 6:30 for the game. 
</P>
<P>
The game, however, had been officially ruled a forfeit at 6:15. 
</P>
<P>
LaBorde reversed the decision, allowing the game to be rescheduled, pending 
arrangements. But those arrangements could not be made. ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
