<P>
Part A; Page 36; Column 3; Foreign Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
56 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEXICO CITY FACING HOLIDAY TRASH CRISIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEXICO CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Christmas trash crisis threatens Mexico City. 
</P>
<P>
The holidays are expected to generate at least 50,000 extra tons of garbage at 
a time when many sanitation workers are on vacation, the Mexico City daily 
Excelsior said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Even in normal times, this sprawling city of more than 15 million has trouble 
coping with garbage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
