<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
William &amp; Mary Coach Jimmye Laycock changed his mind about accepting the 
Boston College coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Laycock, 42, resigned after 11 years at William &amp; Mary to 
take the Boston College job. The school had scheduled a Thursday news 
conference to present the new coach. 
</P>
<P>
Laycock's salary at William &amp; Mary is $73,000. Sources have said that he 
could have earned upward of $200,000 at Boston College. 
</P>
</TEXT>
