<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: MOORPARK; 
</P>
<P>
DEVELOPER TO BUILD COMMUNITY CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Plans for a large shopping center in Moorpark have been approved by the City 
Council under the condition that the developer also builds a $1-million 
community center for the city. 
</P>
<P>
Under the plan approved by the City Council Wednesday night, Santa Monica-based 
Urban West Communities will construct a 122,000-square-foot shopping center at 
the southwest corner of Tierra Rejada Road and Mountain Trail Street. 
</P>
<P>
The developer will also build an 8,000-square-foot community center at nearby 
Arroyo Vista Park. 
</P>
<P>
The community center will include meeting rooms and a gymnasium that can also 
be used as a theater, said Tom Zanic, vice president of Urban West. 
</P>
<P>
Zanic said he would meet with city officials in the coming weeks to discuss 
plans for the center. He said he did not know when construction would begin. 
</P>
<P>
The developer probably will break ground in the spring on the shopping center, 
which will be next to Urban West's Mountain Meadows subdivision, Zanic said. He 
said the plan is for the shopping center to open by December, 1991. CARLOS V. 
LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
