<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTING ANNOUNCED FOR MARTHA GRAHAM TROUPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PASLES, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Martha Graham Company has announced casting for its Jan. 4-6 engagement at 
the Orange County Performing Arts Center in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
Jan. 4, 8 p.m.: "Appalachian Spring" (Copland) -- the Bride: Christine Dakin, 
the Husbandman: Donlin Foreman, the Pioneering Woman: Maxine Sherman, the 
Revivalist: Lyndon Branaugh. 
</P>
<P>
"Deep Song" (Cowell): Joyce Herring. 
</P>
<P>
"Temptations of the Moon" (Bartok): Crescent Moon: Thea Nerissa Barnes; Velvet 
Night: Steve Rooks. 
</P>
<P>
"Maple Leaf Rag" (Joplin): Terese Capucilli, Floyd Flynn, company. 
</P>
<P>
Jan. 5, 8 p.m.: "Diversion of Angels" (Dello Joio): Couple in White: Sherman, 
Foreman; Couple in Red: Kathy Buccellato, Kenneth Topping; Couple in Yellow: 
Debra Kantor, Christopher Dolder; Fourth Man: Mark Borneman. 
</P>
<P>
"Steps in the Street" (Wallingford Riegger): Laura Jimenez, company. 
</P>
<P>
"Herodiade" (Hindemith) : A Woman: Dakin, Her Attendant: Denise Vale. 
</P>
<P>
"Acts of Light" (Nielsen): Conversation of Lovers: Sherman, Topping; Lament: 
Capucilli, company; Ritual to the Sun: Sherman, Topping, company. 
</P>
<P>
Jan. 6, 2 p.m.: "Appalachian Spring": Herring, Flynn, Vale, Dolder. 
</P>
<P>
"Deep Song": Capucilli. 
</P>
<P>
"Temptations of the Moon" and "Maple Leaf Rag": same as on Jan. 4. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets: $13 to $40. (Student rush tickets one hour before each performance, 
subject to availability: $7.) Information: (714) 556-2787. 
</P>
