<TEXT>
<P>
AUTO FOCUS: Thousands of cars are broken into every year, above, but there are 
ways to avoid becoming a statistic. Since many car burglars are after stereos, 
you can protect yourself by using pull-out stereo mounts and removing the 
player when your car is unoccupied, says Costa Mesa Police Detective Darell 
Freeman. 
</P>
<P>
Common sense helps too. Park in well-lighted, occupied areas and use audible 
alarm systems. "Burglars hate to be heard and seen," Freeman says. 
