</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pittsburgh Penguins today traded right wing Rob Brown to the Hartford 
Whalers in exchange for right wing Scott Young. 
</P>
<P>
Brown had six goals and 10 assists in 25 games with the team this season. 
</P>
<P>
Brown, 22, had 112 goals and 142 assists in 124 games with the Penguins. 
</P>
<P>
In 34 games with the Whalers this season, Young posted six goals and nine 
assists. 
</P>
<P>
Young, 23, has scored 49 goals and 89 assists in 197 games with the Whalers. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot, 190-pound right wing played on the U.S. hockey team in the 1988 
Olympics. 
