<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
OPRAH GIVES $50,000 TO AID POOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oprah Winfrey is giving $50,000 to Glide Memorial United Methodist Church, 
which appealed for help in its holiday grocery giveaway to the poor, the church 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"Because she is a very caring person who reaches out to the poor, she 
immediately responded," the Rev. Cecil Williams, the church's pastor, said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Glide Memorial has distributed thousands of bags of groceries to the poor since 
1979. But Williams reported earlier this week that holiday contributions were 
down 37% from 1989 and asked the public for donations. 
</P>
<P>
Winfrey learned of the appeal through poet Maya Angelou, a member of Glide 
Memorial, and called Williams to say she will be sending a check, the church 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The church planned to start its holiday giveaway of more than 10,000 bags of 
groceries today. The church said that while donations have declined, the need 
for the groceries has risen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
